    {
      "id": "65bb7603_3f110bb0",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/api/impl/utils/data/operation/ResourceDataOperationRequestUtils.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 126,
      "message": "I'm very skeptical that this @Async even works in most places we use it.\n\nI ask Copilot, it says:\n> No, the @Async annotation in Spring does not work for static methods. It is specifically designed for non-static methods within Spring beans.\n\nFrom what I read previously, it has serious limitations due to the Spring Proxy-based mechanisms (Spring has to intercept the call to see the @Async at runtime), e.g.\n- it only works on public instance methods of Spring-managed beans\n- self-invocation doesn't work - i.e. if you call from the same class, call won't be proxied and hence won't be async",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-03-14 13:30:49.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "fc84a92c_b8982097",
      "unresolved": true
    },
